1. In application directory, edit models.py.

  <code>
    from django.db import models

    # Create your models here.


    class Topic(models.Model):                                      # Creates Topics table
        topic_name = models.CharField(max_length=264, unique=True)  # Creates topic_name column

        def __str__(self):                                          # Returns string object
            return self.topic_name
            
     
  </code>
  
2. Run following commands in given sequence:
  
  i. python manage.py migrate
  ii. python manage.py makemigrations
  iii. python manage.py migrate
  
  
3. To check if the changes are reflected: (can skip this step)
    
   Run following commands:
   
   i. python manage.py shell
   ii. from polls.models import Topic
   iii. print(Topic.objects.all())                # <QuerySet []>
   iv. t = Topic(topic_name="Searching")
   v. t.save()
   vi. print(Topic.objects.all())                 # <QuerySet [<Topic: Searching>]>
   
   
4. To create the super user for database for first time:

    i. python manage.py createsuperuser
    Username (leave blank to use 'yogeshdatir'): yogesh
    Email address: yogdat@gmail.com
    Password:
    Password (again):
    
5. Go to http://127.0.0.1:8080/admin to manage further operations as needed.
